text: Grafton High School (abbreviated as GHS) is a secondary school in Grafton, New South Wales, Australia. == History == Grafton High School was established on 1 January 1912 and opened on 1 July. A new building opened on 17 May 1915. Since at least the 1960s, the head of an Egyptian mummy has been kept by the school. == References == == Other websites == * Category:Buildings and structures in New South Wales Category:Buildings and structures completed in the 20th century Category:Schools in Australia Australia Category:20th-century establishments in Oceania Category:1910s establishments in Australia Category:1912 establishments
